               
                                   K6 run Command Details
                            install k6 using command "brew install k6"
Step 1:                                                                      
*********------------------------Required Command & Variables------------------------*********
K6_PROMETHEUS_RW_USERNAME=<USER_NAME> \
K6_PROMETHEUS_RW_PASSWORD=<YOUR_VALID_TOKEN> \
K6_PROMETHEUS_RW_SERVER_URL=<SERVER_URL> \
k6 run -o experimental-prometheus-rw main.js

Step 2:
*********----------------------- -How to Retrieve the Details-------------------------*********
1. Login to Grafana K6 → https://grafana.com/
2. Click on "Details" under "Manage your Grafana Cloud stack".
3. Under "Prometheus", click "Details".
4. Scroll to "Grafana Data Source settings":
   → Copy the "User" field  
      K6_PROMETHEUS_RW_USERNAME=<k6_username>

5. In the "Password" field → click "Generate now".
   → Enter a "Token name" → click "Create token".  
   → Copy the token  
      K6_PROMETHEUS_RW_PASSWORD=<generated_api_token>

6. Copy the "URL" field  
      K6_PROMETHEUS_RW_SERVER_URL=<server_url>

*********---------------------------Now you can run the command-------------------------*********      
Step 3: Example Command 
    K6_PROMETHEUS_RW_USERNAME=<USER_NAME> \
    K6_PROMETHEUS_RW_PASSWORD=<YOUR_VALID_TOKEN> \
    K6_PROMETHEUS_RW_SERVER_URL=https://prometheus-prod-xx-prod-ap-south-1.grafana.net/api/prom/push \
    k6 run -o experimental-prometheus-rw main.js

*********---------------------------Import K6 Dashboard in Grafana-------------------------*********  
Step 4: Import K6 Dashboard in Grafana
1. Go to Grafana instance → Dashboards.
2. Create a folder named "K6" (if not present).
3. Click "New" → "Import".
4. Enter 18030 in the "Load" field → click "Load".
5. In "Prometheus" field → select default data source.
6. Click "Import".


*********-------------------------------------View Test Results-----------------------------*********
1. Update time range filter → "Last 1 hour".
2. Run tests locally.
3. View reports in Grafana Cloud → K6 Dashboard.

*********-------------------------View Test Results In Local Like Allure---------------------*********
  Use the following command
    - K6_WEB_DASHBOARD=true K6_WEB_DASHBOARD_EXPORT=./_reports/k6_report.html k6 run main.js
  You can see the reports in the _reports folder as K6_report.html.
